-- Auto-Drive Assist: Predictive Proximity Engine & Dynamic Bezier Waypoints (v6.1)
-- LocalScript: StarterPlayer > StarterPlayerScripts
--
-- v6.1 - memory/FPS leak fixes:
--   * FIXED: raycast direction sign was inverted (turning left extended the
--     RIGHT rays instead of the left, and the car steered toward the
--     "unsafe" side). Negated the angle fed into fromAxisAngle so ray
--     geometry now matches the left/right convention used everywhere else
--     (steerBias, confidence vote, manual-override coloring, status text).
--   * FIXED: rebuildIgnoreList() was firing on every single
--     DescendantAdded/Removing signal from the vehicle (exhaust smoke, skid
--     marks, sounds, etc. fire this constantly), each time doing a full
--     GetDescendants() walk + new table allocation - this was the actual
--     source of the "gets slower forever, drags FPS/terrain streaming down"
--     leak, and it ran regardless of CONFIG.Enabled. Now debounced: watchers
--     just flip a dirty flag, and the real rebuild runs at most twice a
--     second (IGNORE_LIST_REBUILD_INTERVAL) instead of on every event.
--   * FIXED: applyAcceleration() also called GetDescendants() every single
--     frame just to find Thrust/Motor parts. Folded into the same cached
--     pass as the ignore list (cachedThrustParts), rebuilt on the same
--     debounced schedule instead of every Heartbeat.
--   * FIXED: disconnectVehicleWatchers() cleared vehicleWatchConnections but
--     left the same Connection objects sitting permanently in the global
--     `connections` table, so every vehicle reselect leaked 2 dead entries
--     for the rest of the session. Now removed from both lists together.
--
-- v6.0 - confidence-based steering + adaptive raycasts:
--   * Standard Assist (and headless Auto-Navigate cruise) no longer steers off
--     a raw repulsion vector. It now votes: every ray is classified "safe" (green)
--     or "danger" based on GreenThreshold, tallied separately per side, and the
--     two sides' safe-fractions are compared. The car only commits to a side when
--     the margin between them clears DecisionConfidence (e.g. 70% safe left vs
--     30% safe right = a confident call). A near-even split (a "coin flip") no
--     longer produces a random-looking swerve - it holds straight instead.
--   * Raycasts are no longer fixed-length/fixed-angle. Each ray's length and
--     angle now adapt smoothly (frame-to-frame lerp, never a snap) to current
--     steering intent (manual input if you're steering, otherwise the assist's
--     own applied turn):
--       - Driving straight: front-facing rays extend (spot things sooner ahead),
--         edge rays pull in slightly and fan out a touch wider (better peripheral
--         coverage for cross traffic / walls coming up at corners).
--       - Turning either direction: rays on the side you're committing to
--         extend, the front rays and the opposite-side rays shrink - so the
--         sensor budget goes toward the direction you're actually going, not
--         wasted on space you're turning away from.
--   * All of the above is tunable from the new "Raycasts" settings tab.
--     General/behavior settings moved to a separate "Other" tab. Press
--     RightShift any time to show/hide the whole settings panel.
--   * (carried over from v5.9) fixed the per-frame ignore-list rebuild that
--     caused the script to get laggier the longer it ran, cleared stale thrust
--     force references on vehicle reselect, and stopped rays that hit nothing
--     from generating fake threat/steering at speed.

